  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Maybe we should validate the commit message format only in after_success from travis. Thus allowing pushes to check for passing tests before checking for the commit message format. Should be better?\n\nThe issue with `after_success` is that it doesn't affect the build result. I think it's OK to fail because of a commit message and without running the tests, no?\n",
