  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I think it's OK to fail because of a commit message and without running the tests, no?\n\nIt will be a pain for developers in the end, maybe we can just run the check AFTER the tests, that was initially what I wanted to do.\n\nKnowing that the tests are passing here is way more important than having the commit message check failing right away (a bit like asking for lint before tests, it's a pain).\n\nI wish travis exposed ways to have multiple status checks (https://github.com/blog/1227-commit-status-api) but no. The only way to have something better is to make a contribution bot run and do checks inside various status checks (like jsdelivr does). This way you can see that the tests are passing but not the commit check.\n\nFor now, checking the commit status after the tests should be enough to keep a good flow.\n",
